      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "krea2_regional_multilora_v3  (v3 = LoRA masking + Reference Lock)\n=============================================================\nSame chain as V2. Node 6 is the NEW v3 node: every region row\nnow has a 'load ref image' button with an inline thumbnail.\n\nWHAT v3 ADDS:\n  Each region can carry a REFERENCE IMAGE (the 'mold'). Its\n  VAE latent steers that box's in-progress latent toward the\n  reference every step during the guidance window - identity\n  anchoring on top of the LoRA masking. Ref-only rows (no\n  LoRA) work too: the box is molded toward the image.\n\nHOW TO USE:\n  1. Node 6: one row per character (LoRA + strength).\n  2. Click 'load ref image' on a row -> pick the character's\n     reference. Thumbnail appears on the node.\n  3. Node 5: draw one box per row IN THE SAME ORDER.\n  4. VAE must be wired into node 6 for refs to work.\n  5. Queue.\n\nKNOBS:\n  ref_strength 0.3   = pull per step (0.2-0.4 sane, 0.7 paste)\n  ref window 0-0.6   = guide early, release late. Shorter end\n                       (0.4) = looser pose copy from the ref.\n  ref_feather 0.06   = mask edge softness.\n  Set ref_strength 0 to disable refs entirely (pure v1 mode).\n\nNOTE: reference guidance couples pose+framing to the ref image\ninside the box (Tier-1 'latent mold'). Crop refs to face/torso\nfor identity without full-pose lock."
      ],
      "title": "README v3",
      "color": "#444",
      "bgcolor": "#222"
    }
